    <td>Target for this lesson?</td>
    <td>To help our classmates improve their game</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Did I reach my target? </td>
    <td>Yes </td>
  </tr>
</table>


<table>
  <tr>
    <td>How did you use your learning habits this week?</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Persevering</td>
    <td>I was confused what feedback to give but I kept trying and I got there.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Questioning?</td>
    <td>There weren't any questions to be asked.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Independence</td>
    <td>I didn’t need any help on the task given</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Reflecting</td>
    <td>I improved my evaluation after thinking how it could be better.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Engagement</td>
    <td>I kept my head down and worked, completing the task given.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>What could have gone better in your learning?</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>I could have asked the person who designed the game about the purpose before playing.</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>What changes do you need to make to improve your learning next time?</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>To keep going until the time is up and don’t get even a little bit distracted when working.</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
